public co.cask.cdap.proto.metadata.lineage.LineageRecord getLineage(co.cask.cdap.proto.Id.DatasetInstance datasetInstance,

                                                                      Integer levels)

        Retrieves Lineage for a given dataset.

        datasetInstance - the dataset for which to retrieve lineage
        startTime - start time for the query, in seconds
        endTime - end time for the query, in seconds
        levels - number of levels to compute lineage for, or null to use the LineageHandler's default value
        Returns:
        LineageRecord for the specified dataset.

        endTime - end time for the query, in seconds, or in 'now - xs' format
        collapseTypes - fields on which lineage relations can be collapsed on
        levels - number of levels to compute lineage for, or null to use the LineageHandler's default value
        Returns:
        LineageRecord for the specified stream.
        Throws:
        IOException
        co.cask.cdap.common.UnauthenticatedException
        co.cask.cdap.common.NotFoundException
        co.cask.cdap.common.BadRequestException
        co.cask.cdap.security.spi.authorization.UnauthorizedException
